the' b'powerful enemies of the world of truth (that is, the world of the spirit, and' b'of asha), astvatereta will look upon the whole of corporeal existence and' b'render it imperishable. he and his comrades will engage in a great battle with' b'the forces of evil, which will be destroyed.' b'the name astvatereta is clearly the result of theological speculation' b'(kellens, as are those of his two brothers, ukhshyatereta, "he who makes' b'truth grow," and ukhshyatnemah, "he who makes reverence grow"; the names of the' b'three virgins (yashts who are impregnated with the seed of zarathushtra' b'when they bathe in lake kansaoya and give birth to the saoshyants, are equally' b'speculative. each of these saoshyants will arrive at the beginning of a' b'millennium, initiating a new age and a new cycle of existence; astvatereta will' b'appear in the third and final millennium to save mankind.' b'the doctrine of the future savior had already taken shape in the archaemenid' b'period (sixth to fourth century bce). it was not, perhaps the principal element' b'in the formation of the messianic idea, but it was certainly a determining' b'factor, one that enjoyed great success in the hellenistic period beyond the' b'confines of the iranian world. a similar concept, that of the future buddha,' b'maitreya, was most likely indebted to it, and christian messianism can trace' b'its roots to the same source.' 